<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-275-316  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 275 316.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>InfoWorld  March 26 1990 v12 n13 p26(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>True Type is generations ahead of Adobe Type Manager. (Tech Talk)(column)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Gibson, Steve.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The strange alliance between Apple and Microsoft Corp to produce astandard font rendering system can be easily explained when onerealizes just how advanced the True Type technology is.andP;  True Typecan render format fonts three to eight times faster than Adobe'sType Manager system, and True Type is much more flexible andextensible.andP;  In fact, the only thing giving Adobe a chance in themarket is IBM's curious decision to favor Adobe's technology inthe SAA platform.andP;  IBM is not doing its customers any favors byendorsing the sixth generation of Adobe's technology since thefirm makes obsolete all older generations when it introduces a newone anyway.andP;  Adobe's technology is large, slow and limitedcompared with the Apple/Microsoft solution.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Adobe Systems Inc. (products)Microsoft Corp. (products).andO;Ticker:    MSFT; ADBE.andO;Product:   Truetype (Computer font) (design and construction)Type Manager (Printer software) (design and construction).andO;Topic:     FontsComparison.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>